      "_launchReducedProfileNote": "WIDENED launch profile derived 2026-06-03 from r5-launch-reduced-2026-06-02 per the operator's 'widen launch-active runway' directive. Adds 4 experimental_reward_active surfaces (evidence_bundle, coreference, relation_lifecycle, noise_suppression) to the 3 core_reward_active surfaces + 1 guardrail. Flag changes vs. r5-launch-reduced-2026-06-02: enableEvidenceBundleAtoms false→true; policyEvidenceAllowedActions ['bundle']→['bundle','include','boost','suppress']. Coreference + relation_lifecycle do not require additional flags — they ride on the existing policyRelationTypedAdmission + policyQueryConditionedAdmission pipeline once the parseQueryRelationIntent and categoryLensBFS gate fixes land (commits in the corresponding code change). Experimental promotion is justified by substrate-viability + bounded-safety: A100 widened confirmation produced 0 gold damage / 0 off-family worst across 30+ cells but ALSO 0 measured solo lift on hand-written candidates — the substrate is admitted, atoms decode, no damage, but Qwen does not rerank the admitted candidates higher because gold docs were already top-K via direct retrieval. Per orchestrator framing: 'CoreTex is meant to be experimental and malleable. The right bar is substrate viability + bounded safety, not maximum solo lift from our hand-written candidate.' Bundle hash changes vs the calibration-time 0x2d953b71; operator regenerates manifest at launch time. See release/calibration/2026-05-21-memory-corpus-v2/SURFACE_SEARCH_HARNESS_REPORT_V2_CORRECTION.md (widened-runway addendum) for the underlying evidence.",
